# Documentation Standards

Good code explains itself. Great code explains **why**.

## Document

- Architecture decisions and trade-offs
- Non-obvious business rules
- Public module APIs / manifests when the repo uses them
- Runbooks for deploy, migrations, smoke tests

## Do not document

- What the next line obviously does
- Stale comments that drift from code
- Duplicate README walls for every tiny change

## Comments

Prefer clear naming. Comment only intent, constraints, or dangers.

## Agent rule persistence

When the user says ثبتها / “don’t make me say this again”, encode the correction into `.cursor/rules` — not a chat-only apology.
